cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper discusses the performance of question answering components over the DBpedia knowledge graph, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, since DBpedia is a large-scale knowledge graph, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, since the paper evaluates the behaviour of different components, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as well.
